📂 Python File Organizer

A simple Python automation script that organizes files in a folder into categorized subfolders such as Images, Documents, Videos, Music, and Others.

This project helps automate file management by scanning files in a directory and sorting them into folders based on their file extensions.

🚀 Features
	•	Automatically organizes files into folders
	•	Supports multiple file types
	•	Creates folders automatically if they do not exist
	•	Reduces manual effort in sorting files
	•	Beginner-friendly Python automation project

  ⚙️ How It Works
	1.	The script asks the user to enter the folder path to organize.
	2.	It scans all the files inside the folder.
	3.	It checks the file extension of each file.
	4.	Based on the extension, the file is moved to the appropriate folder.

